						<p>Pāṇḍya, Jaṭāvarman Śrīvallabha, 34th year = 14th Century.</p>						

						<p>The trustees of the temple of Tiruvēṅgavāchal comprising the <hi rend="italic">dēvakaṉ</hi>mi, accountant, the <hi rend="italic">śrīkāriyam</hi>, and the <hi rend="italic">māṭāpattiyam</hi> fixed the dues to be paid on some <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> land in possession of a <hi rend="italic">maṟava</hi> individual of Maṭa-mayilāppūr in Peruvā-nāḍu.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 639.]</p>						

